SUMMARY<br>
Renowned for merging the worlds of art, fashion and pop culture with candy, Dylan's Candy Bar is the largest, state-of-the-art sweets emporium. Dylan's Candy Bar is not your average "candy store" as it's home to over 7,500 candies from around the world, making it the most popular destination for the ultimate sugar rush experience. Giant Pop Art installations of oversized candy adorn the store and transport visitors to a modern day Candy Land, awakening the creative spirit and inner child in everyone.<br>
<br>
Dylan's Candy Bar stores are currently located in New York City, East Hampton, Los Angeles, Miami Beach and Chicago. Dylan's Candy Bar products can also be found in prestigious venues like Neiman Marcus, W Hotels, Four Seasons Hotels and the Empire State Building. For more information, please visit www.DylansCandyBar.com or www.facebook.com/DylansCandy.<br>
<br>
<br>
JOB DESCRIPTION<br>
The Inventory Manager is responsible for understanding, implementing and enforcing the retail process. The position must deliver consistent leadership that will ensure the quality of our product. The retail process includes planning, scheduling and overseeing all aspects of retail merchandise.<br>
<br>
ESSENTIAL JOB FUNCTIONS<br>
•	Ensure accuracy and organization of the store's inventory<br>
•	Completes store operational requirements by scheduling and assigning Inventory Associates; following up on work results<br>
•	Provide timely and accurate inventory data<br>
•	Help ensure and maintain proper item codes, descriptions, cost data, and bill-of materials by working closely with the buying and merchandising teams<br>
•	Monitor data exchanges between three operating systems to ensure integrity and work with all data providers to maximize value of information produced<br>
•	Train employees to use the inventory system and reporting features<br>
•	Coordinate and execute periodic cycle counts and year-end physical inventory<br>
•	Install and ensure "best practices" for receipt of inventory and purchase order procedures <br>
•	Special focus on seasonal product to avoid over and under stock positions<br>
•	Consistently improve inventory turn of core products<br>
•	Manage product expiration and dating issues<br>
•	Assist in managing other areas of the store<br>
•	Coach and train the Inventory staff to reach their full potential<br>
•	Work closely with the Merchandising team to ensure items stay in stock and floor moves can be executed properly<br>
•	Ensure the stockroom and its surrounding area is a clean and organized work space<br>
•	Order product directly through vendor or inventory team at the corporate office<br>
•	Communicate stock needs to members at corporate<br>
•	Monitor levels of product mark-out and damages<br>
•	Report and analyze shrink<br>
•	Cycle counting and variance resolution<br>
•	Support shortage resolution<br>
•	Identifying and resolving process / team / individual accuracy issues<br>
•	Coordinate annual inventory cut-off reconciliation<br>
•	Perform other duties as assigned<br>
<br>
SKILLS & QUALIFICATIONS<br>
•	3-5 years experience in Inventory Control Management in a retail store a MUST<br>
•	Bachelor's degree in related field<br>
•	Excellent computer skills, particularly Excel<br>
•	Ability to communicate professionally and effectively to a diverse audience<br>
•	Consensus builder and excellent negotiating skills<br>
•	Strategic thinker able to thrive in a group environment<br>
•	Ability to manage Store Sales and inventory teams effectively<br>
•	Ability to provide outstanding customer service<br>
•	Ability to maintain a fair, consistent set of standards as they apply to a non-exempt workforce <br>
•	Ability to adjust priorities and manage time wisely in a fast-paced environment<br>
•	Ability to maintain records and documentation pertaining to workforce<br>
•	Comfortable in a rapidly growing, fast paced environment<br>
•	Must have the ability to work a fully flexible retail schedule including openings, closings, weekends and holidays<br>
•	Availability to travel, as needed<br>
•	The incumbent must be very energetic<br>
•	Appreciation of Dylan's Candy Bar unique culture, entrepreneurial attitude, heritage and passion for its products<br>
    </section>

